! Changelog

!! Version 0.0.19

!!! Code Cleanup

* ''Removed All Logging'' - Eliminated all console.log/warn/error statements from source and plugins
** Cleaner production code without debug output
** Affected files: language.ts, engine.js, edit-text.js, emoji-picker.js, zen-mode startup, keymap plugins, lint.js, plugin-combiner.js

!!! Infrastructure

* ''Fixed Clean Script'' - `npm run clean:plugins` no longer deletes plugin.js files
** Previously the script incorrectly removed required plugin.js files
** Now only removes generated .js.meta files and lang-tiddlywiki.js

* ''Source File Restructuring'' - Renamed TypeScript source files for clarity
** `tiddlywiki-parser/` → `parser/`
** `parser-utils.ts` → `utils.ts`
** `language-support.ts` → `extensions.ts`
** `codemirror-index.ts` → `codemirror.ts`
** `codemirror-tiddlywiki.ts` → `compat.ts`
** `tiddlywiki-plugin-entry.ts` → `plugin.ts`

* ''Extended NPM Scripts'' - New convenience scripts for development
** `npm run clean:all` - Clean dist and plugins
** `npm run build:all` - Build everything
** `npm run rebuild` - Clean all and rebuild
** `npm run rebuild:tiddlywiki` - Clean plugins and rebuild
** `npm run dev` - Watch mode for TiddlyWiki plugin development

* ''Updated Dependencies'' - Fresh npm install with latest compatible versions

---

!! Version 0.0.18

!!! Bug Fixes

* ''Multiline Macro Attributes'' - Attributes in multiline macros now parse and highlight correctly
** Previously `<<tabs\n    explicitState:""\n>>` would not highlight `explicitState:""` as an attribute
** Block-level macro parser now always looks for `>>` on subsequent lines

* ''Autocomplete Flickering'' - Fixed dropdown constantly re-rendering
** Root cause: `languageData.of()` callback in engine.js was returning new array/object references on every state change
** CodeMirror interpreted this as completion sources changing, triggering constant re-evaluation
** Fix: Cache the wrapper objects and return same references

* ''Duplicate Completions'' - Fixed widgets like `<$list` appearing 4 times
** TiddlyWiki language was being registered twice (via `registerLanguage()` and `codeLanguages`)
** Now filtered from `codeLanguages` loop to prevent duplication

* ''Escape Key Not Closing Popup'' - Autocomplete popup now closes on Escape
** Previously Escape was handled by TiddlyWiki, closing the tiddler instead
** Now checks for both "active" and "pending" completion states

* ''Transclusion Field/Index Completion'' - Fixed `{{tiddler!!field}}` and `{{tiddler##index}}` completion not working
** Plugin entry point was missing `getTiddlerFields` and `getTiddlerIndexes` callbacks
** Fixed TiddlyWiki language being re-initialized without callbacks when used as nested code language
** `getCodeParser` now skips TiddlyWiki to avoid circular re-initialization

* ''Filter Text Reference Completion'' - `{tiddler!!field}` now only triggers inside filter contexts
** Single-brace text references only complete inside `[...{`, `{{{...{`, or `filter="...{`
** Double-brace transclusions `{{tiddler!!` still work anywhere

* ''Snippets Don't Interfere'' - Snippet completions no longer trigger during field/index completion
** Snippets are suppressed when typing `{{tiddler!!` or `{{tiddler##`

---

!! Version 0.0.17

!!! New Language Plugins

* ''9 New Languages'' - Extended language support for syntax highlighting
** Lezer (grammar definition language)
** WAST (WebAssembly Text format)
** Rust
** Sass/SCSS
** Go
** PHP
** C++
** Java
** LaTeX

!!! Linting Improvements

* ''Per-Tiddler Lint Toggle'' - Disable/enable linting on a per-tiddler basis via toolbar button
** New toolbar button to toggle linting for the current tiddler
** Uses temporary tiddlers (`$:/temp/codemirror-6/lint-disabled/`) - settings are session-based
** Visual feedback: button appears dimmed with strikethrough when lint is disabled
** Linting reconfigures dynamically without reload when toggled

* ''JSON Linting'' - Built-in JSON syntax validation using CodeMirror's `jsonParseLinter`
** Highlights JSON syntax errors in real-time
** Shows lint gutter markers for quick error identification

!!! Bug Fixes

* ''External Link Parsing'' - `[ext[url]]` now correctly distinguished from filter runs
** Similar to `[img[`, prevents `[ext[` from being misinterpreted as a filter operand
** Tiddler completion no longer triggers inside external links

* ''URL Auto-Links'' - Extended protocol support for automatic URL highlighting
** Now supports: `mailto:`, `tel:`, `ftp:`, `file:`, `geo:`, `data:`, `javascript:`
** Previously only `http://` and `https://` were recognized

* ''Emoji Picker'' - No longer triggers after URL protocols
** Typing `mailto:na` no longer shows emoji completions for `:na`
** Checks for common URL protocols before activating

* ''Editor Placeholder'' - Placeholder text now displays when editor is empty
** Uses CodeMirror 6's `placeholder()` extension
** Shows the configured placeholder from `editPlaceholder` widget attribute

!!! Improvements

* ''Tag-Based Language Detection'' - Fixed tiddler list resolution in language tag configuration
** `hasConfiguredTag` now uses `wiki.filterTiddlers()` instead of `parseStringArray()`
** Properly resolves tiddler lists stored by the tag-picker widget

!!! Infrastructure

* ''Plugin Dependencies'' - All plugins now declare dependency on main editor plugin
** Added `dependents` field to all plugin.info files

* ''MIME Type Documentation'' - Added `$:/language/Docs/Types` tiddlers for all supported content types
** Enables proper MIME type display in TiddlyWiki's content type picker

* ''Naming Convention Documentation'' - Documented `cm6-lang-*` startup module naming convention
** Allows TiddlyWiki language module to dynamically discover language dependencies

---

!! Version 0.0.16

!!! Bug Fixes

* ''Enter Key on Empty Lists'' - Always removes list marker when pressing Enter on empty list line
** Simplified logic removes complex markdown-style "tight list" conditions
** Works consistently for all list types (bullet, numbered, mixed)

* ''Auto-Close Tags in Attributes'' - No longer inserts closing tags inside attribute values
** Detects when cursor is inside `AttributeValue` or `AttributeString` nodes
** Fixes issue with `<$text text="<$set>">` incorrectly inserting `</$text>`

* ''Color Picker List Detection'' - Correctly identifies indented numbered lists
** `#hexcolor` with only whitespace before it is treated as a list marker, not a color
** Checks for whitespace between line start and `#`

* ''Incomplete Block-Level Macros'' - `<<macro` on its own line now highlights correctly
** Previously, incomplete macros at block level were not parsed/highlighted
** Now shows opening mark `<<` and macro name with proper syntax highlighting
** Multi-line incomplete macros also handled correctly

!!! New Features

* ''Typed Block Syntax Highlighting'' - Code blocks with file extensions now highlight correctly
** `$$$.js`, `$$$.css`, `$$$.ts`, `$$$.py`, etc. now use appropriate language highlighting
** Supports common file extensions: `.js`, `.mjs`, `.ts`, `.tsx`, `.css`, `.html`, `.json`, `.md`, `.py`, `.sql`, `.xml`, `.yaml`, `.yml`, and more

* ''Filter Run Prefix Completion'' - Completes with closing bracket
** `:filter`, `:map`, `:reduce`, etc. now complete to `:filter[]` with cursor inside brackets
** Only adds closing bracket if not already present

!!! Linting Improvements

* ''Built-in Variables'' - Linter now recognizes TiddlyWiki built-in variables
** `currentTiddler`, `storyTiddler`, `transclusion` no longer flagged as undefined

* ''Updated Lint Message'' - More accurate undefined definition message
** Changed from "possibly undefined macro" to "possibly undefined variable / macro / procedure / function"

!!! UI Improvements

* ''Toolbar Icon Sizing'' - Fixed toolbar button icons not fitting properly
** Added flexbox styles and proper SVG sizing (`1em × 1em`)
** Added `cm6-icon` class to all plugin icons for CSS specificity
** Icons now use `fill: none` to work correctly with various toolbar styles

!!! Documentation

* ''Plugin Readmes'' - Added readme.tid to 12 plugins that were missing documentation
** editor, emoji-picker, plugin-combiner, and all lang-* plugins now have readme files

* ''Comprehensive README.md'' - Complete rewrite of project documentation
** Full feature list, installation guide, configuration options
** Complete keyboard shortcuts reference
** Developer guide for creating plugins
** Build instructions and project structure

---

!! Version 0.0.15

!!! New Features

* ''CSS Support in `<style>` Tags'' - CSS syntax highlighting and autocompletion inside `<style></style>` tags
** Works like fenced code blocks - switches to CSS parser for content
** Requires lang-css plugin to be installed
** lang-tiddlywiki now loads after other language plugins to enable nested language support

